Look at the inside of the egg shells at 2:34 everyone. The pink stain is not the correct color of real blood. Also, real blood that originated from the inside of the eggs would not look as neatly dyed, like a one color Easter egg. If it were real blood that came from the eggs the shells would have some spots with more blood that would look darker and some spots with less blood that would look lighter. Also, eggs with babies don't even look like that. There's way too much "blood" in the eggs Rob used. In a fertilized egg with that much liquid the colors are still clear and yellow. The blood is in blood vessels, which are small red lines in the yellow yolk. So relax guys. This is obviously fake. If you don't believe me, look up images of real fertilized eggs.
you can tell at 2:05 that the liquid is clear/white

Having raised chickens from eggs, I can confirm that the eggs were fake. First off, no bird that flies is able to lay eggs that are that large. Second, if the eggs were real there would be veins all over the place and the blood would not be as thick of dark. Depending on the stage that the eggs are in there would be more of the chick developed in a real egg. Also the nest was so clearly fake and bought at a store.

Okay, idiots lets get this straight. Those are not real eggs, this is coming from someone with experience with bird eggs. First of all no nested bird egg is that big, they're literally normally the size of a larger milk dud. Second of all a bird egg would normally not contain blood unless the baby bird was disfigured, it would contain a translucent milky yellowish substance. Finally, unless the bird was in early development the embryo would not look like a glob. It's obvious it was just food coloring and some gelatinous substance inserted into the egg right at the cut from where he drilled into it.

For all you guys being all like, "THOSE ARE REAL EGGS, YOU JUST KILLED BABY BIRDS OMG AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH" Here are reason they are obviously NOT REAL -The nest was in the tree, which means a bird who lives in a tree made that nest. Birds that like in trees are mainly small, so their eggs would be the size of a quail egg. -Chicken eggs from the grocery store were put in the nest, mother birds that live in trees cannot make an egg the size of a chicken egg. -It was red inside because he dyed it red with food dye. -The chunks in it were probably the egg yolk  -Rob wouldn't of been allowed to upload this video if the eggs were real -Rob is REALLY good at jokes. I noticed something from the comments that I found confusing. "The eggs are fake." Incorrect. The eggs are not fake. The eggs are 100% real (the inside was not hard to color red). Obviously, they did not come from a bird's nest. They are genuine, legitimate, store-bought chicken eggs. The *eggs* are real.ï»¿  Tiny edit: Clearly, this must be said. The egg shells are real. Sure, the egg shells aren't the entirety of the egg, but neither are the insides: the yolk, the white, and whatever the hell else. So, when I say "egg", I am referring to the shell because that is the subject of this video. It should not have to be that specific.

Before one comments their outrage about Rob's "animal cruelty" we should take a minute to logically process the visible evidence. First I'm quite certain that most flying birds, especially the ones found in CA are much too small to lay eggs that large. Secondly as many people noted, the blood wouldn't have stained the inside of the egg like dye would. Thirdly, the omelette with the empty egg carton seems like pretty convenient evidence that he didn't steal eggs from his backyard. Fourthly lets count how many eggs we see in the video, we are shown an empty 6 egg carton when we are shown the omelette that could quite have easily taken three eggs by itself, and we watch him open two eggs with their "bloody" contents and then a third empty one for decorating. Another thing to note is when he is using the dremel tool to open the back of the eggs, the liquid shooting out looks like normal yoke coloring, so he very likely dropped in dye right before he used pliers to pull out the broken shell. Lastly we all know Rob to be a goofster and a gaffster, so I think we can all assume that no real harm came to any animals; people are not stupid for having shocked reactions to Rob's somewhat macabre humor.

Rob works for an actual company. If the eggs were real, he would get in major trouble with organizations like PETA and other companies. His job would be at risk and he might have even gotten sued, who knows? The point is, of course the egg-from-the-backyard bit was planned. The typical songbirds egg size is small, like around quarter coin size (http://www.sialis.org/images/eggscircle3.jpg). Anything larger would be at risk from the weight of the egg versus the strength of the nest and branch. The eggs were pre-planted brown chicken eggs that he stuck in a nest he either made, bought, or found abandoned. The "blood" and "bird parts" can be explained through food coloring and cotton or other semi-solid and absorbant materials that he put in between screen cuts.
